I don't see onnx.proto ,either.You may need download it from onnx project.
onnxruntime follows the [onnx](https://github.com/onnx/onnx) rules,I nerver compiled success from source(So I changed to using nuget which is smoothy for me).For more infomation, you may want to wait the team's member answer.

Hi, @Debottam !
I'am not shure, but I guess you can try this [example](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/docs/C_API.md). 
Unfortenatly, I'm getting error 
```code
 error: ‘OrtGetAllocatorWithDefaultOptions’ was not declared in this scope
   CHECK_STATUS(OrtGetAllocatorWithDefaultOptions(&allocator));
```
when trying to compile with ` g++ -Lonnxruntime-linux-x64-0.5.0/lib -o api_sample api_sample.cpp -I onnxruntime-linux-x64-0.5.0/include -lonnxruntime`. 
maybe it helps

As i can see, my problem was related to [renaming](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/1615/files):
`OrtCreateDefaultAllocator->OrtGetAllocatorWithDefaultOptions`

@Debottam, have you downloaded libs from release page?

@nlyf,

Hi @nlyf 

The current lib file I have is what you can see in https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/tree/master/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/ but it doesn't have any *.so file, do I need to find some other directory??

Hi @nlyf,
I would like to mention how I am building onnxruntime, I want you to correct if I am missing anything here for that may be its not generating ant onnxruntime.so file
So I am following this link for building onnxruntime https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/BUILD.md
step1:
git clone --recursive https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime
cd onnxruntime
step2:
Install cmake-3.13 or better from https://cmake.org/download/.
step3:
./build.sh --config RelWithDebInfo --build_shared_lib --parallel

btw using the onnxrutime built above I am able to run it in python but having trouble in C++. Need help

Thanks in advance,
Debottam.
